[1] Massachusetts: State DPH urges measles vaccination as suspected cases triple
Date: 2 May 2019
Source: Mass Live [abridged, edited]
https://www.masslive.com/news/2019/05/measles-vaccination-urged-as-massachusetts-suspected-cases-triple.html


More than 60 suspected cases of measles, with one confirmed, have been investigated by the Massachusetts Department of Health to date this year [2019]. The DPH said in comparison it investigated 21 suspect cases during the same period last year and none were confirmed measles.

The largest national number of confirmed measles cases in 25 years has been reported this year [2019] to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. The 704 cases of measles in 22 states is the largest number since the highly contagious disease was considered eliminated in the United States in 2000 as a result of vaccination. The count is nearly double the total of confirmed cases reported nationally last year.

Contributing factors in a country where overall immunization is high include parental fears over vaccination, pockets of low immunity and global travel at a time of large outbreaks of measles in both developed and developing countries.

[Byline: Anne-Gerard Flynn]

