[2] Alabama
Date: Thu 2 May 2019
Source: AL [abridged, edited]
https://www.al.com/news/2019/05/600-people-contacted-after-unvaccinated-measles-patient-travels-to-alabama-mississippi-tennessee.html


600 people contacted measles after an unvaccinated patient traveled to Alabama, Mississippi, and Tennessee.

Four additional cases of measles, all linked to the original source, have also been reported in Tennessee. The cases are part of a larger national outbreak that includes more than 700 cases in 22 states.

[Byline: Leada Gore]

