[13] Nepal (Morang, Dang and Kapilvastu)
Date: Wed 1 May 2019
Source: Reliefweb from The Kathmandu Post [abridged, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/nepal/measles-outbreak-morang-dang-and-kapilvastu-raises-concern


Two weeks ago, the World Health Organization published an alarming report that measles cases across the world rose 300 percent in the 1st 3 months of 2019 compared to the same period last year [2018].

"While this data is provisional and not yet complete, it indicates a clear trend," said the United Nations health agency.

Nepal has made significant strides in vaccination, but measles outbreaks in some districts have become a cause for concern.

Multiple officials the Post spoke to said measles outbreaks were reported in Morang, Dang and Kapilvastu districts in April 2019 alone.

Measles was endemic in Nepal, and an average 90 000 cases were recorded every year from 1994 to 2004. Routine measles vaccination began in the country in 1979 with 3 districts. The campaign was expanded nationwide after 10 years.

Over 13 000 children aged 9 months-15 years in disease-hit areas are being immunised, officials say.

[Byline: Arjun Paudel]

